commentTextItems.html: lofted to long-off, takes two runs for that

commentPostTextItems.html: That marks the 27 runs win for the West Indies. 14 runs scored by Murphy off the last over.
Zimbabwe were never in the match after losing the first two wickets. Scoring slowed down considerably and they paid the price for that
There was a five ball over in this innings, which made no difference to the final outcome any ways.
Andy Blignaut could have made the difference, but he was unlucky to be run out after being send back by campbell
We will be back with you with all the live action tomorrow at 0700 GMT, India will take on the home team Zimbabwe.
Kindly send in your opinions/comments to comms@cricinfo.com

stories.summary: Rangana Herath was just named Man of the Series for a one-match series, but that's not the strangest match award that's been handed out

stories.title: 1st Match, West Indies v Zimbabwe, Coca Cola Cup, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1727th ODI in cricket history

stories.title: How sweet it is
stories.summary:
It hasn't been often of late that an opposing captain has acknowledged
his team was beaten batting, bowling and fielding by the West Indies

stories.title: West Indies clinch 27-run victory in Coca-Cola Cup opener
stories.summary:
A good all-round performance by West Indies brought them a 27-run
victory over a demoralized but defiant Zimbabwe team at Harare Sports
Club in the opening match of the triangular tournament also involving
India
